"http://linkedin.com/company/allrecipes.com"
]
}
,"name": "Chocolate Waffles"
,"aggregateRating": {
"@type": "AggregateRating",
"ratingValue": "4.4",
"ratingCount": "236"
}
,"cookTime": "PT15M"
,"nutrition": {
"@type": "NutritionInformation"
,"calories": "226 kcal"
,"carbohydrateContent": "36 g"
,"cholesterolContent": "54 mg"
,"fiberContent": "1 g"
,"proteinContent": "4 g"
,"saturatedFatContent": "4 g"
,"sodiumContent": "290 mg"
,"sugarContent": "21 g"
,"fatContent": "8 g"
,"unsaturatedFatContent": "0 g"
}
,"prepTime": "PT10M"
, "recipeCategory": ["Breakfast"]
,"recipeCuisine": ["American"]
,"recipeIngredient": [
"1.5 cups all-purpose flour",
"0.5 cup white sugar",
"3 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder",
"3 teaspoons baking powder",
"0.5 teaspoon salt",
"1 cup milk",
"2 large eggs",
"4 tablespoons butter, melted",
"1 tablespoon butter, softened",
"0.75 cup confectioners' sugar",
"0.5 teaspoon vanilla extract",
"1 teaspoon milk",
"nonstick cooking spray" ]
,"recipeInstructions": [
{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/YuPvjCwWSdSUuSQjdo8Kd-rrDac=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/ALR-24141-chocolate-waffles-i-VAT-step-01-1dc597a7a5c540249b5cad752f134815.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Gather all ingredients. Preheat a waffle iron."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ei2tZ0SvG6A3-sr9bj9YagMGWl8=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/ALR-24141-chocolate-waffles-i-VAT-step-02-1-a85c0ad870624a90a2cfe213003af2c4.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Make waffles: Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and salt in a large mixing bowl. Stir in milk, eggs, and butter until the mixture is smooth."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/74pPuFigZZleY-UitHvrGqVANeM=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/ALR-24141-chocolate-waffles-i-VAT-step-03-ccab55ffdaf04aacbdf42e4d9ef7720c.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Make hard sauce: stir together softened butter, confectioners&#39; sugar, vanilla extract, and milk. Sauce should be fairly stiff. Set aside."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/1WLtY4n-wH0d1YDqjY1-yKhjL84=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/ALR-24141-chocolate-waffles-i-VAT-step-04-9b4aad06a6b14263b8af73359f5e723a.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Spray preheated waffle iron with nonstick cooking spray. Pour waffle mix onto hot waffle iron. Cook until golden brown."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/RNkjw3lKGvPM9dSBQFUENSw6K7M=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/ALR-24141-chocolate-waffles-i-VAT-step-05-1d12cb523a5a46b4abd5ad8a6668d85e.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Serve hot with hard sauce."
} ]
,"recipeYield": ["10", "10 waffles"]
,"totalTime": "PT25M"
,"review": [
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "LISSALU"
}
,
"reviewBody": "I will rate this a four because I made changes... but with my changes I would rate it a 5!! The changes I made were 2 tsp baking powder, 1/2 cup cocoa powder, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 1 tsp vanilla and half a bag of chocolate chips. So yummy! I made this in my belgian waffle maker and they turned our wonderful! I served this with Easy Whipped Cream from this site. I made the leftovers and froze them. I think I will try them for dessert with ice cream next!"
},
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Mariapem"
},
"reviewBody": "This made a super decadent Sunday morning breakfast. Based on others comments and my previous experience with my Belgian waffle iron, I added 2 extra T of cocoa for more chocolatey goodness, used veg oil instead of melted butter, added 1 t of vanilla, 1/4 c extra milk and beat the egg whites separately to add a bit of lift to the waffles. They turned out crisp and moist. My teenagers smeared choc hazelnut spread and peanut butter before sandwiching two together. Topped with the best Canadian maple syrup, it was pure decadence.",
"datePublished": "2019-01-13T14:48:33.750Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Kemp Hoversten"
},
"reviewBody": "According to my 14-year-old, this was like having chocolate lava cake for breakfast. Huge hit. I followed the suggestions of LISSALU and went with the 2 tsp of baking powder, 1/2 cup of dark chocolate cocoa powder, 1/2 tsp of baking soda, and 1 tsp of vanilla. I had a nervous moment because the batter seemed more like brownie batter or muffin batter (very thick) but when I put it on the waffle irons, it turned out to be really wonderful. We cooked a Belgian and we made smaller ones on the Dash waffle iron and both were great. My girls asked for this recipe to go into the regular rotation for “fun breakfasts”.",
"datePublished": "2020-07-18T19:24:31.097Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Aimee"
},
"reviewBody": "The first time I made it, the only change I made was that I added 1/2 t cinnamon. They were good. The second time I followed someone's advice and used oil and added the cinnamon. We all felt they had a chocolate cake doughnut flavor. My oldest really likes them, so we will keep it like that. Very easy to make. However, next time I may try to incorporate buttermilk, sour cream or yogurt to help moisten them.\nUPDATE: I switched the milk to 1 1/2 c. buttermilk and about 2/3 c. milk and it did help moisten the waffles, but my kids liked the cake doughnut flavor over the more moist waffle. (This was for a double batch.)\n11/12- Okay, just follow the directions- for a Belgium waffle, cook 5- 6 min. MAKE THE SAUCE! You have oreo waffles - kids love them!",
"datePublished": "2018-02-19T14:26:57.970Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Luv2Tweak"
},
"reviewBody": "My 9 year old daughter asked me to make chocolate waffles so i looked up a recipe on here...this was a very good recipe, we all loved it. Did make th glaze. Topped with fresh strawberries, powder sugar and a drizzle of chocolate syrup..YUM! I did put in 1/3 cup cocoa powder, and separated the egg whites beat until stiff peaks and folded in the battter at the end...you won't be sorry for doing this step...makes for a light fluffy waffle. As i was eating this i was thinking how good this would be with ice cream and hot fudge...next time :)",
"datePublished": "2010-04-22T16:49:57.640Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "sandrabe"
},
"reviewBody": "This is a great recipe. The only thing I did different was separate the eggs. I whipped the egg whites to a peak and folded them into the batter. I have a feeling this will be a do over many times. Put some fresh fruit on top and enjoy.",
"datePublished": "2019-05-07T15:08:03.960Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "mayura"
},
"reviewBody": "yum yum! I used 1/4 cup of cocoa powder, 2 tsp of baking powder, 1/2 tsp of baking soda, and oil instead of melted butter. I freeze them and then pop them into the toaster. Crunchy outside, soft inside with great chocolaty flavor.",
"datePublished": "2011-02-14T22:07:00.863Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Amity34"
},
"reviewBody": "Good but not real sweet. I ended up changing a few things due to goodies we had on hand and all I can say is wow that was an awesome dessert! First I used coconut butter instead of melted butter in a silly attempt to make them slightly healthier. Then I used the new dark chocolate cocoa powder and made a syrup with it too by adding about 1T coconut butter, 1T cocoa, 2T Agave and some water to thin. We ate ours with whipped cream coconut shreds, the chocolate syrup, and a few pecan pieces. OMG to die for! My 2.5 year old ate 2 without batting an eye. I would say it was a hit!",
"datePublished": "2011-06-17T18:44:59.660Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Melissa Conger"
},
"reviewBody": "These were yum! I added 1/4 C more cocoa powder and subtracted the same amount of flour. After I made one and tasted it, I added 3/4t vanilla and a little more sugar. Also used oil instead of butter. I skipped the 'hard sauce' and instead made simple syrup with sliced strawberries as a sauce. The only reason I gave this 4 out of 5 stars is it wouldn't have been chocolatey enough for me as written, and the vanilla was a great addition. Hubby said it would be better for dessert than breakfast-but that was HIS opinion. For a dessert, I'd also add fresh whipped cream! My waffle iron gave me 8 or so waffles, so I wrapped the extras in parchment and put them in a freezer bag and froze them.",
"datePublished": "2012-11-17T11:42:50.673Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "JovialOrzo7618"
},
"reviewBody": "I made all of the suggestions that Lissalu recommended and added a 1/4 cup of chia seeds (so I can kid myself into thinking they are healthy) and upped the milk just a bit. They turned out great. I made them in my mini waffle maker and they would make a perfect ice cream sandwich.",
"datePublished": "2023-07-04T16:22:48.475Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "ScottFamily"
},
"reviewBody": "We thought these were great. I didn't get a chance to make the hard sauce, but I'm sure that would really gild the lily, I think we'll save it for a special treat (well, an even more special treat than chocolate waffles already are to begin with!). My children really enjoyed these and they helped make a yucky morning more fun. We didn't even need syrup! The only change I made was to substitute white whole wheat flour for part of the ap flour so they would be a little healthier (you can't tell by the taste). Thanks for the great recipe! ETA: I had a little batter leftover and used it to make pancakes with mini chocolate chips for dessert, they were great! My kids asked for more and were really disappointed that we ran out of batter. :)",
"datePublished": "2010-04-29T05:32:17.090Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "jewelleeherrin"
},
"reviewBody": "My grandkids eat these waffles just about everyday! Very easy to make and we love the flavors ✅",
"datePublished": "2025-12-28T20:46:16.831Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "ANTHONY"
},
"reviewBody": "I ABSOLUTELY LOVE IT",
"datePublished": "2025-11-14T19:08:14.076Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "EGM"
},
"reviewBody": "Kids love this recipe!!! Added orange extract and they said it tastes like delicious cake.",
"datePublished": "2025-07-19T13:29:21.830Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "3"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "GoldenAcai4829"
},
"reviewBody": "Batter was too thick and was missing flavor.",
"datePublished": "2025-01-04T17:33:00.652Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Ivorysmooth"
},
"reviewBody": "Added 1/2 tsp vanilla extract to the waffle mix. Also recommend doubling the hard sauce ingredients. Doesn’t make much.",
"datePublished": "2024-12-21T18:25:48.225Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Deni"
},
"reviewBody": "Added chocolate chips!",
"datePublished": "2024-12-10T17:55:54.504Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Aylin42"
},
"reviewBody": "It's good \"as is\". No, it is not overly sweet. Yes, some vanilla would probably enhance the chocolate flavor. (It is a recipe with only cocoa for the chocolate flavor - it will be subtle rather than fudgey.) I chose to top mine with a drizzle of raspberry syrup and it was very good. I found it didn't seem to cook evenly on my waffle iron but I have not determined the cause yet. I liked it very much and will use it again. If you really want super-chocolatey flavor, you will want to add melted chips, baking chocolate (will need other recipe changes), or topping with a chocolate syrup or even ganache. As is, it is appropriately crispy and fluffy. For me, I would love more of a fruit and cream sort of topping, or even a nice fruit compote. It's just right for bringing out fresh toppings such as this. It could even be topped with ice cream and fudge sauce if that is more to your liking. I would actually give it a 4.5 rather than a 4, but that isn't an option.",
"datePublished": "2024-11-12T19:18:25.950Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Karenc60"
},
"reviewBody": "I took LISSALU's advice (see reviews) and made those changes. Wow! What fantastic tasting, tender waffle! I'm keeping this recipe. Definitely a crowd pleaser.",
"datePublished": "2024-09-01T00:11:24.985Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Hanan"
},
"reviewBody": "Amazing recipe , my kids loved it and you can save it for later in freezer .",
"datePublished": "2024-08-25T18:09:54.709Z"
}
]
